description:
In this episode of ANN Profiles, Alyssa Truman and Gregory Whitsett, Adventist Mission planning director, converse about the remarkable path of spiritual growth and mission work. Whitsett shares his experiences, from his early years to his impactful missionary work in Laos and Thailand, and his current role in guiding global mission initiatives. This episode offers a deep insight into the challenges and joys of being a missionary and how faith plays a crucial role in navigating life's journey.

The Seventh-day Adventist Church has been an established denomination since 1863. It is a global Christian family with over 21 million members who hold the Bible as the ultimate authority. We are believers who promise to help people understand the Bible to find freedom, healing, and hope in Jesus.
